  "prompt": "What is scuba diving?",
  "response": "Scuba diving is an underwater activity where a person uses a self-contained underwater breathing apparatus (SCUBA) to breathe and explore underwater environments like oceans, lakes, and rivers. Divers wear specialized equipment including:\n\n1. Scuba tank - Provides compressed air or specialized breathing gas mixtures\n2. Diving mask - Allows clear underwater vision\n3. Fins - Help with swimming and movement\n4. Wetsuit or drysuit - Provides thermal protection\n5. Buoyancy control device (BCD) - Helps manage underwater depth and floating\n6. Regulator - Delivers breathable air from the tank\n\nScuba diving can be done for various purposes, such as:\n- Recreation and exploring marine life\n- Scientific research\n- Photography\n- Underwater archaeology\n- Commercial and professional diving\n- Military operations\n\nDivers must undergo training and certification to learn safety procedures, equipment use, and underwater techniques.",
